  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana consists of multiple interconnected layers:\n\n1. **GitHub Ownership Definition** (.github/CODEOWNERS): The central GitHub file that defines code ownership patterns, mapping file paths to GitHub teams and users using glob patterns.\n\n2. **CI Validation** (.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml): A GitHub Actions workflow that validates the CODEOWNERS file on every pull request to main branch. It uses the mszostok/codeowners-validator action to check for files, patterns, syntax, and ownership gaps with checks like 'duppatterns' and experimental checks for 'notowned' and 'avoid-shadowing'.\n\n3. **Go Feature Management Type** (pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go): Defines a Go type `codeowner` with 36 constant string values that map to GitHub teams and users. This integrates CODEOWNERS information into Grafana's feature management system, allowing features to be tied to specific teams like @grafana/grafana-app-platform-squad, @grafana/dashboards-squad, etc.\n\n4. **Manifest Generation Infrastructure** (scripts/codeowners-manifest/): A complete JavaScript-based pipeline that parses and indexes CODEOWNERS data:\n   - **index.js**: Main orchestrator that combines all generation steps with smart caching based on SHA-256 hashes of the CODEOWNERS file and all tracked git files. Prevents unnecessary regeneration when content hasn't changed.\n   - **raw.js**: Generates raw audit data by invoking the `github-codeowners` CLI tool with JSONL output format for efficient stream processing.\n   - **generate.js**: Processes the raw audit data into three indexed JSON files: teams.json (list of all codeowners), teams-by-filename.json (file->owners mapping), and filenames-by-team.json (owners->files mapping) for fast lookups.\n   - **metadata.js**: Creates metadata.json with generation timestamp and SHA-256 hashes for cache validation.\n   - **constants.js**: Central configuration defining all manifest file paths.\n\n5. **npm Script Integration**: package.json defines npm scripts that orchestrate the pipeline:\n   - `codeowners-manifest`: Runs the complete manifest generation with caching\n   - `codeowners-manifest:raw`: Generates raw audit data\n   - `codeowners-manifest:generate`: Processes raw data into manifests\n   - `codeowners-manifest:metadata`: Generates metadata\n   - `test:coverage:by-codeowner`: Runs test coverage scoped by codeowner\n\n6. **Jest/Test Integration** (jest.config.codeowner.js and scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js): Extends Jest to enable running tests and coverage reports by codeowner. The config reads the filenames-by-team.json manifest to filter test files belonging to a specific team (TEAM_NAME env var), enabling per-team coverage metrics and reports."
}

